Out of 127 collected fecal samples from diarrheic calves, 119 (93.7%) bacterial isolates were recovered, including 23 (18.1%) Salmonella serovars and 96 (75.6%) E. 
coli strains (Table 2
).

PCR results revealed that out of the tested 10 E. 
coli serogroups, 7 serogroups (70%) possessed ETEC virulence gene (K99) including O26, O44, O78, O86, O111, O119 and O127 while O103, O157 and O158 not possessed K99 gene (Fig. 2
).
